	</p><p class="cs1CE9D70E"><span class="csB0C9F1E0">2026 </span><span class="csC2FEE544">REGULAR SESSION</span></p><p class="cs709C557D"><span class="csC2FEE544">Introduced</span></p><p class="cs3E63B65"><span class="cs8498B7A6">Senate Bill 713</span></p><p class="csFF933113"><span class="csADC6E5DB">By Senator Chapman</span></p><p class="cs8BEF69CE"><span class="cs7B75DFFE">[Introduced February 2, 2026; referred<br/>to the Committee on Education; and then to the Committee on Finance]</span></p><p class="cs29F66C3F"><span class="csEF05ACC">A BILL to amend and reenact &sect;18A-4-2 and &sect;18A-4-8a of the Code of West Virginia, 1931, as amended, relating to providing for a 10 percent pay raise for all public school staff.</span></p><p class="cs63FD752D"><span class="cs93AB6E8B">Be it enacted by the Legislature of West Virginia:</span></p><p class="cs53FB8D75"><span class="csEF05ACC">&nbsp;</span></p><h2 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="cs7A33E2F1">ARTICLE 4. SALARIES, WAGES AND OTHER BENEFITS. </span></h2>
	<h4 class="cs89687900">
		<span class="csB9803513">&sect;18A-4-2. State minimum salaries for teachers.</span></h4>
